## Interview Cheatsheet

```
Q: What is the state?
A: up[v] and down[v] = count of valid sequences of
   current length ending at value v

Q: Why prefix sums?
A: To compute sum over a range in O(1) instead of O(m)
   Reduces each length step from O(m²) to O(m)

Q: Why up[v] = pref_down[v-1]?
A: To extend UP to v, previous move must be DOWN
   at some value strictly less than v
   That is sum of down[0..v-1] = pref_down[v-1]

Q: Why down[v] = total_up - pref_up[v]?
A: To extend DOWN to v, previous move must be UP
   at some value strictly greater than v
   That is sum of up[v+1..m-1]
         = total_up - pref_up[v]
```
